                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/601: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Chairman of the American Delegation to the General Disarmament
                        Conference (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GHS1" type="to"
                            >Gibson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-04T00:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1932—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. [For <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">Wilson</persName>.] Your 53,
                    December 2, 6 p.m. As indicated in previous telegrams I consider it highly
                    desirable and important that the League adopt a resolution along the lines of
                    the proposal stated in “(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) (1)” of your telegram. Now
                    that there is available in the <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1"
                        >Lytton</persName> Report the findings as to fact it seems that mere
                    reaffirmation of the League Resolution of March 11 would constitute a step
                    backwards and that the entire logic of the situation calls for a step forward
                    definitely applying the doctrine of lion-recognition to “Manchoukuo”.</p>
                <p>I do not however desire that you take any initiative in bringing this view to the
                    attention of the representatives of the governments members of the League but
                    you should, in case you are approached by any such representative[s], advocate
                    this view.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
